ur les hommes québécois portant sur leur réalité sociale et leur santé et bien-être ainsi que sur les politiques, les services et les interventions à mettre en place pour répondre à leurs besoins.  aMode of access: Internet via World Wide Web.  aIn French.0 aDescription based on online resource; title from PDF title page (publisher's Web site, viewed 26. Apr 2024) 0aMen--Health and hygiene--Quâebec (Province). 7aSOCIAL SCIENCE / Anthropology / General.2bisacsh1 aCazale, Linda, eeditor.4edt4http://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/edt1 aCloutier, Richard, eeditor.4edt4http://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/edt1 aLebeau, Aimé, eeditor.4edt4http://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/edt1 aRoy, Jacques, eeditor.4edt4http://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/edt1 aTremblay, Gilles, eeditor.4edt4http://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/edt08iTitle is part of eBook package:dDe GruytertACUP Complete eBook-Package 2017z978311127365508iTitle is part of eBook package:dDe GruytertACUP Upgrade eBook-Package 2017z978311127619940uhttps://doi.org/10.1515/978276373073840uhttps://www.degruyter.com/isbn/9782763730738423Coveruhttps://www.degruyter.com/document/cover/isbn/9782763730738/original  a978-3-11-127365-5  ACUP Complete eBook-Package 2017b2017  a978-3-11-127619-9  ACUP Upgrade eBook-Package 2017b2017  aGBV-deGruyter-alles